#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:2
msgid "General guidelines for course content"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:6
msgid ""
"If you are copying and pasting content over from a Word or PDF document, "
"you may find that extra (unnecessary) styling is also copied over into "
"the HTML editor field in Moodle. To remove this use the 'clear "
"formatting' option in the Moodle editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:10
msgid ""
"These are some general rules of thumb that we have found useful when "
"developing courses so they ‘look good’ on the mobile device, although "
"clearly much depends on the screen size of the devices your learners are "
"using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:13
msgid "Number of sections/topics per course module: up to 10 sections/topics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:14
msgid ""
"Activity titles: we’ve found that about 4-6 words max will work best when"
" displayed on the mobile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:16
msgid ""
"Number of activities per section/topic: up to 10 activities. There is no "
"requirement for a particular order of activity types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:18
msgid ""
"Course/Activity icons: although there are generic icons for each activity"
" type, your course will look more attractive if you can add custom "
"icons/images for each activity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:21
msgid ""
"Length of page content: as a rough guide approx 200-250 words is the most"
" that will fit on each page, otherwise the user may need to do a lot of "
"scrolling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:23
msgid ""
"Images: try to keep the filesize of images down as far as possible, "
"although the course/activity icons are automatically resized on export, "
"other images contained within the activities are not. Best to keep an "
"image files below about 400px wide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:27
msgid ""
"Media content: long videos may be uncomfortable to view on a small "
"screen, we suggest keeping videos quite short (less than 3-5 mins). "
"Consider splitting you videos into different parts if you really need to "
"include long video content. As with images, try to keep the video "
"filesize as low as possible, users are unlikely to need very hi-res "
"versions of videos if they are viewing on a 4″ screen. We use Handbrake "
"to convert our videos, using the ‘Android’ preset – this always gives a "
"good balance between video quality and the filesize."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guidelines.rst:35
msgid ""
"File resources: we discourage including long pdf files or presentation "
"type files for 2 main reasons, (1) it can be hard to read long "
"pdfs/presentations on smaller screens and (2) users may need to have "
"specific apps installed to open these types of files."
msgstr ""

